-- Shanghai Pharmaceuticals Shares Surge After Announcing Acquisition Plans
-- B y   B l o o m b e r g   N e w s
-- 2010-11-30T01:50:03Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2010-11-30/shanghai-pharmaceuticals-shares-surge-after-announcing-acquisition-plans.html
Shanghai Pharmaceuticals Holding Co.
shares surged by the daily limit in Shanghai trading after plans
by the Chinese drugmaker to acquire China Health System Ltd.  The shares rose 10 percent to 26.19 yuan as of 9:47 a.m. on
the Shanghai stock exchange, the highest price since the shares
listed in March 1994.  Shanghai Pharmaceuticals agreed to buy a 55.45 percent
stake in China Health System to expand its distribution network
nationwide, according to a statement to exchange.  To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Bloomberg News at 
 gturk2@bloomberg.net  